t, Washington]]\n[[Category:Cities in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Cities in Snohomish County, Washington]]\n[[Category:County seats in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Industrial Workers of the World]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1890]]\n[[Category:Populated places on Puget Sound]]\n[[Category:Port settlements in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:1890 establishments in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Cities in the Seattle metropolitan area]]\n", "name_user": "SounderBruce", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSports:citation moved", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everett,_Washington"}
{"title_page": "Pixelmetrix", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Pixelmetrix Corporation\n| logo =[[File:Pixelmetrix logo.jpg|Company pixmet]]\n| type = [[Private company|Private]]\n|foundation = {{Start date|1999}}\n|location_city       =[[Singapore]]\n|area_served      = Worldwide\n|founder       = Danny Wilson, CEO\n| industry = Television Broadcasting\n|products         = TV network monitoring\n| homepage = http://www.pixelmetrix.com\n}}\n\n'''Pixelmetrix Corporation'''<ref name=\"AUTOREF\" /> is a company that develops preventive [[Network monitoring|monitoring]] products for [[Terrestrial television|terrestrial]], [[Satellite television|satellite]], [[Cable television|cable]], and [[IPTV]] networks. The company is known for its DVStation product, and also provides equipment and [[network intelligence]] systems to [[Broadcasting|television broadcasters]] for the management and monitoring of \"[[Quality of Service]]\" and \"[[Quality of Experience]]\". Pixelmetrix is headquartered in Singapore, and also has offices in the United States and Europe.\n\nFollowing a liquidation exercise starting in 2014, the Pixelmetrix legal entity was dissolved in 2017. From 2014, full hardware and software support for all Pixelmetrix product lines has been provided by [http://www.torquevideo.tv Torque Video Systems].\n\n== Corporate history ==\nIn 1999, Danny Wilson and Ben Lim founded Pixelmetrix Corporation in [[Singapore]] as a privately held limited company, recruiting Tom Orlowski and Hideki Takahashi to complete the start-up team.<ref name=\"AUTOREF1\" /> The name \u201cPixelmetrix\u201c was derived from the combination of the words \"pixel\" and \"metrics\", loosely suggesting that the company \"measures pixels\".\n\nPixelmetrix released its first product, DVStation, in 2000. DVStation is a [[Modularity|modular]] multi-player system that can simultaneously monitor up to 21 ports and multiple layers of the [[Broadcasting|video transmission]] chain.\n[[Image:DVStation wiki.jpg|thumb|alt=DVStation |DVStation, the first Pixelmetrix product developed in 2000]]\n\nIn 2002, Japan Telecom and Korea Telecom selected DVStation for end-to-end [[Signal integrity|signal quality]] monitoring during the [[FIFA World Cup]] Football games in Japan and Korea.<ref name=\"AUTOREF2\" /> In 2004 the DVStor and DVShift Compliance Recording product lines were introduced to target [[disaster recovery]]. With the emergence of [[IPTV]],<ref name=\"AUTOREF3\" /> Pixelmetrix launched DVStation-IP<sup>3</sup> in 2006 for IPTV test and monitoring. The following year, it brought on the Electronic Couch Potato and Consolidator to monitor true customer viewing to ensure \"[[Quality of Experience]]\".<ref name=\"AUTOREF4\" />\n\nBy October 2001, Pixelmetrix had opened an office in Switzerland and established a sales office in Florida.<ref name=\"AUTOREF5\" />  The company added a support office in Barcelona, Spain in 2010.\n\n==Finance==\nThe company has pursued external funding and today is backed by several [[Angel investor|private]], [[venture capital]] and [[institutional investor]]s including OWW Capital Partners, UOB Ventures, Enspire Capital and [[Singapore Economic Development Board]] Technopreneur Investment Fund. Revenues have grown year on year and the company has been profitable throughout the years.\n\n==Awards==\nPixelmetrix has been conferred the TV Technology STAR Awards (Superior Technology Award Recipient) 2012,  2009, 2007, 2004 and 2000, Cable & Satellite International Highly Commended Product of the Year Award 2010, Frost & Sullivan Industrial Technologies Award (2009),<ref name=\"AUTOREF7\" /> C+T Technology Development Award 2009, Cable & Satellite International Product of the Year Award 2008, Engineering & Technology [[Emmy Award]] (2007),<ref name=\"AUTOREF6\" /> Broadcast Engineering publication Pick Hit Awards 2008 and 2005, BIRTV Product of the Year Award 2006, Cable-Satellite/Mediacast Product of the Year Awards 2004 and 2003, as well as the [[International Association of Broadcasting Manufacturers|IABM]] Peter Wayne Award for Best Design and Innovation (2000).\n\n==Product lines==\nPixelmetrix has five major product lines:\n\n*DVStation Monitoring Platforms\n*DVStor - Compliance Recording, Disaster Recovery, House of Worship Solution\n*DVStation-IP<sup>3</sup> - IPTV Monitoring Platform\n*Electronic Couch Potato (ECP)<ref name=\"AUTOREF8\" />\n*Consolidator - Network Management System\n*OTT Media Grinder (OMG) - Validation System for Over-The-Top Delivery Infrastructure \n*Pelican Video Encoders\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF\">{{Cite web|url= http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=2904488|title= Pixelmetrix Corporation|publisher=Bloomberg Businessweek|date= |accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF1\">{{Cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/091999singapore-tech.html | title=In Singapore, the Start-Up Dance Is Still Difficult to Do | first=Wayne | last=Arnold | work=[[New York Times]] | date=1999-09-19 | accessdate=2011-01-20}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF2\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.scopus.ru/info/8/42|title=Pixelmetrix DVStation Selected for Signal Monitoring at 2002 FIFA World Cup Korea/Japan|publisher= Scopus Video Networks|date=2002-04-04|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF3\">{{Cite news|url= http://www.koreaittimes.com/story/pixelmetrix-danny-wilson-managing-quality-service-panel-session-iptv-world-forum-london|title=Pixelmetrix Danny Wilson in Managing Quality of Service Panel Session at the IPTV World Forum, London|publisher= Korean IT Times|date=2009-03-25|accessdate=2011-01-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF4\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.tvover.net/2010/04/01/Pixelmetrix+Electronic+Couch+Potato+To+Monitor+Virgin+Medias+Digital+Television+Network.aspx|title=Pixelmetrix Electronic Couch Potato to Monitor Virgin Media's Digital Television Network|publisher= TVover.net|date=2010-04-01|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF5\">{{Cite web|url= http://pixelmetrix.com/PressCenter/press%20release/PixelmetrixExpandUSfinal.pdf|title=Pixelmetrix Expands Sales Organization to Market DVStation in the United States|publisher= Pixelmetrix|date=|accessdate=2011-01-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF6\">{{Cite web|url= http://broadcastengineering.com/news/pixelmetrix-receive-technical-emmy-0920/|title= Pixelmetrix to receive Technical Emmy|publisher= Broadcast Engineering|date=2007-09-20|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF7\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.asiaone.com/Business/SME%2BCentral/Tete-A-Tech/Story/A1Story20090821-162521.html|title= Start-ups win technology award|publisher= The Straits Times, Singapore Press Holdings|date=2009-08-23|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF8\">{{Cite web|url= http://broadbandgear.net/2010/12/pixelmetrix-advanced-video-technology-leader/|title= Pixelmetrix: Advanced Video Technology Leader|publisher= BTR Broadband Technology Report|date=2010-12-13|accessdate=2011-01-20}}</ref>\n|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.pixelmetrix.com}}\n*[https://www.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/091999singapore-tech.html New York Times Article on Pixelmetrix]\n\n[[Category:Singaporean brands]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications companies of Singapore]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications companies established in 1999]]\n[[Category:Electronic test equipment manufacturers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Pixelmetrix Corporation\n| logo =[[File:Pixelmetrix logo.jpg|Company pixmet]]\n| type = [[Private company|Private]]\n|foundation = {{Start date|1999}}\n|location_city       =[[Singapore]]\n|area_served      = Worldwide\n|founder       = Danny Wilson, CEO\n| industry = Television Broadcasting\n|products         = TV network monitoring\n| homepage = http://www.pixelmetrix.com\n}}\n\n'''Pixelmetrix Corporation'''<ref name=\"AUTOREF\" /> is a company that develops preventive [[Network monitoring|monitoring]] products for [[Terrestrial television|terrestrial]], [[Satellite television|satellite]], [[Cable television|cable]], and [[IPTV]] networks. The company is known for its DVStation product, and also provides equipment and [[network intelligence]] systems to [[Broadcasting|television broadcasters]] for the management and monitoring of \"[[Quality of Service]]\" and \"[[Quality of Experience]]\". Pixelmetrix is headquartered in Singapore, and also has offices in the United States and Europe.\n\nPixelMetrix is currently \"IN LIQUIDATION \u2010 COMPULSORY WINDING UP (INSOLVENCY)\" according to the Singapore Accounting and Corporate Regulatory Authority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acra.gov.sg/home/|title=Home - ACRA|website=www.acra.gov.sg|access-date=2016-04-15}}</ref>\n\n== Corporate history ==\nIn 1999, Danny Wilson and Ben Lim founded Pixelmetrix Corporation in [[Singapore]] as a privately held limited company, recruiting Tom Orlowski and Hideki Takahashi to complete the start-up team.<ref name=\"AUTOREF1\" /> The name \u201cPixelmetrix\u201c was derived from the combination of the words \"pixel\" and \"metrics\", loosely suggesting that the company \"measures pixels\".\n\nPixelmetrix released its first product, DVStation, in 2000. DVStation is a [[Modularity|modular]] multi-player system that can simultaneously monitor up to 21 ports and multiple layers of the [[Broadcasting|video transmission]] chain.\n[[Image:DVStation wiki.jpg|thumb|alt=DVStation |DVStation, the first Pixelmetrix product developed in 2000]]\n\nIn 2002, Japan Telecom and Korea Telecom selected DVStation for end-to-end [[Signal integrity|signal quality]] monitoring during the [[FIFA World Cup]] Football games in Japan and Korea.<ref name=\"AUTOREF2\" /> In 2004 the DVStor and DVShift Compliance Recording product lines were introduced to target [[disaster recovery]]. With the emergence of [[IPTV]],<ref name=\"AUTOREF3\" /> Pixelmetrix launched DVStation-IP<sup>3</sup> in 2006 for IPTV test and monitoring. The following year, it brought on the Electronic Couch Potato and Consolidator to monitor true customer viewing to ensure \"[[Quality of Experience]]\".<ref name=\"AUTOREF4\" />\n\nBy October 2001, Pixelmetrix had opened an office in Switzerland and established a sales office in Florida.<ref name=\"AUTOREF5\" />  The company added a support office in Barcelona, Spain in 2010.\n\n==Finance==\nThe company has pursued external funding and today is backed by several [[Angel investor|private]], [[venture capital]] and [[institutional investor]]s including OWW Capital Partners, UOB Ventures, Enspire Capital and [[Singapore Economic Development Board]] Technopreneur Investment Fund. Revenues have grown year on year and the company has been profitable throughout the years.\n\n==Awards==\nPixelmetrix has been conferred the TV Technology STAR Awards (Superior Technology Award Recipient) 2012,  2009, 2007, 2004 and 2000, Cable & Satellite International Highly Commended Product of the Year Award 2010, Frost & Sullivan Industrial Technologies Award (2009),<ref name=\"AUTOREF7\" /> C+T Technology Development Award 2009, Cable & Satellite International Product of the Year Award 2008, Engineering & Technology [[Emmy Award]] (2007),<ref name=\"AUTOREF6\" /> Broadcast Engineering publication Pick Hit Awards 2008 and 2005, BIRTV Product of the Year Award 2006, Cable-Satellite/Mediacast Product of the Year Awards 2004 and 2003, as well as the [[International Association of Broadcasting Manufacturers|IABM]] Peter Wayne Award for Best Design and Innovation (2000).\n\n==Product lines==\nPixelmetrix has five major product lines:\n\n*DVStation Monitoring Platforms\n*DVStor - Compliance Recording, Disaster Recovery, House of Worship Solution\n*DVStation-IP<sup>3</sup> - IPTV Monitoring Platform\n*Electronic Couch Potato (ECP)<ref name=\"AUTOREF8\" />\n*Consolidator - Network Management System\n*OTT Media Grinder (OMG) - Validation System for Over-The-Top Delivery Infrastructure \n*Pelican Video Encoders\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF\">{{Cite web|url= http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=2904488|title= Pixelmetrix Corporation|publisher=Bloomberg Businessweek|date= |accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF1\">{{Cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/091999singapore-tech.html | title=In Singapore, the Start-Up Dance Is Still Difficult to Do | first=Wayne | last=Arnold | work=[[New York Times]] | date=1999-09-19 | accessdate=2011-01-20}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF2\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.scopus.ru/info/8/42|title=Pixelmetrix DVStation Selected for Signal Monitoring at 2002 FIFA World Cup Korea/Japan|publisher= Scopus Video Networks|date=2002-04-04|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF3\">{{Cite news|url= http://www.koreaittimes.com/story/pixelmetrix-danny-wilson-managing-quality-service-panel-session-iptv-world-forum-london|title=Pixelmetrix Danny Wilson in Managing Quality of Service Panel Session at the IPTV World Forum, London|publisher= Korean IT Times|date=2009-03-25|accessdate=2011-01-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF4\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.tvover.net/2010/04/01/Pixelmetrix+Electronic+Couch+Potato+To+Monitor+Virgin+Medias+Digital+Television+Network.aspx|title=Pixelmetrix Electronic Couch Potato to Monitor Virgin Media's Digital Television Network|publisher= TVover.net|date=2010-04-01|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF5\">{{Cite web|url= http://pixelmetrix.com/PressCenter/press%20release/PixelmetrixExpandUSfinal.pdf|title=Pixelmetrix Expands Sales Organization to Market DVStation in the United States|publisher= Pixelmetrix|date=|accessdate=2011-01-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AUTOREF6\">{{Cite web|url= http://broadcastengineering.com/news/pixelmetrix-receive-technical-emmy-0920/|title= Pixelmetrix to receive Technical Emmy|publisher= Broadcast Enginee