ools' Annual Hootenanny]] features [[Marc Almond]], [[George Ezra]], [[Junior Giscombe]], [[Jess Glynne]] and others.<ref name=\"2018/19\">{{cite web |title=BBC Two - Jools' Annual Hootenanny, 2018/19 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bx3bmn |website=BBC |accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[24 February]] \u2013 ''Pappano's Greatest Arias'', presented by [[Antonio Pappano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2019/09/soft-cell-say-hello-wave-goodbye|title=Soft Cell: Say Hello, Wave Goodbye|website=BBC Media Centre|access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref>\n*[[1 March]] \u2013 ''Say Hello, Wave Goodbye'', documentary about [[Soft Cell]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0002w72|title=Pappano's Greatest Arias|website=BBC Four|access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref>\n*[[14 April]] \u2013 ''Janet Baker in her own words'', documentary about [[Janet Baker]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/apr/14/rachmaninov-isle-of-the-dead-lpo-jurowski-review-preludes-gilburg-janet-baker-in-her-own-words-bbc4|title=Home listening: Rachmaninov big and small, and a night in with Janet Baker|author=Fiona Maddocks|website=The Guardian|access-date=22 April 2019}}</ref>\n*[[7 September]] \u2013 ''[[Strictly Come Dancing (series 17)|Strictly Come Dancing]]'' 2019 season, introducing new judge [[Motsi Mabuse]]. \n*[[12 October]] \n**''[[The X Factor: Celebrity]]''; competitors include [[Brendan Cole]], [[Martin Bashir]] and [[Hayley Hasselhoff]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/x-factor-celebrity-brendan-cole-ricki-lake-and-ben-foden-among-stars-revealed-for-full-line-up-11823548|title=X Factor: Celebrity - Brendan Cole, Ricki Lake and Ben Foden among stars revealed for full-line up|website=[[Sky News]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref> The series is won by [[Megan McKenna]], with [[Max and Harvey]] second and [[Jenny Ryan]] third.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/11/30/megan-mckenna-