es]] |date=4 January 2019 |accessdate=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[3 January]] \u2013 Donald Froud, orchestral administrator and French horn player, and first general manager of the [[Ulster Orchestra]], 86\n* [[7 January]] \u2013 [[John Joubert (composer)|John Joubert]], South Africa-born composer, 91<ref>{{cite news |title=John Joubert obituary |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/john-joubert-obituary-msw73gm3l |newspaper=[[The Times]] |url-access=subscription  |date=5 February 2019 |accessdate=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[19 January]] \u2013 [[Ted McKenna]], drummer ([[The Sensational Alex Harvey Band]]), 68 (cerebral haemorrhage)<ref>[https://www.loudersound.com/news/ted-mckenna-drummer-with-rory-gallagher-sahb-michael-schenker-dead-at-68 Ted McKenna, drummer with Rory Gallagher, SAHB, Michael Schenker, dead at 68]</ref>\n* [[28 January]] \u2013 [[Noel Rawsthorne]], organist, 89<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/thetimes-uk/obituary.aspx?n=noel-rawsthorne&pid=191422045 | title=Noel Rawsthorne | work=The Times | author= | date=1 February 2019 | accessdate=10 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[6 February]] \u2013 [[Gerald English]], tenor, 93<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.limelightmagazine.com.au/news/gerald-english-has-died/ | title=Gerald English Has Died | work=Limelight Magazine | author=Angus McPherson | date=8 February 2019 | accessdate=10 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[9 February]] \u2013 [[Cadet (rapper)|Cadet]], rapper, 28 (car accident)<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/cadet-dead-aged-28-uk-13973731 Cadet dead aged 28 - UK rapper killed in tragic car accident]</ref>\n* [[25 February]] \u2013 [[Mark Hollis (musician)|Mark Hollis]], 64, singer and songwriter ([[Talk Talk]])<ref>[https://www.nme.com/news/music/mark-hollis-talk-talk-reportedly-died-aged-64-2453863  Talk Talk\u2019s Mark Hollis has reportedly died, aged 64]</ref> (death reported on this date)\n* [[26 February]] \u2013 [[Andy Anderson (drummer)|Andy Anderson]], 68, rock drummer (cancer)<ref>[https://www.nme.com/news/former-cure-drummer-andy-anderson-reportedly-passed-away-aged-68-2454464 Former Cure drummer Andy Anderson has reportedly passed away, aged 68]</ref>\n* [[28 February]] \u2013 [[Andr\u00e9 Previn]] KBE, conductor (past principal conductor of the [[London Symphony Orchestra]] and music director of the [[Royal Philharmonic Orchestra]]), composer, and pianist, 89<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/28/obituaries/andre-previn-whose-music-knew-no-boundaries-dies-at-89.html | title=Andr\u00e9 Previn, Whose Music Knew No Boundaries, Dies at 89 | work=The New York Times | author=James Barron | date=28 February 2019 | accessdate=2 March 2019}}</ref>\n* [[1 March]] \u2013 [[Paul Williams (British singer)|Paul Williams]], singer, 78<ref>[http://dmme.net/paul-williams-passed-away/ Paul Williams Passed Away]</ref>\n* [[3 March]] \u2013 [[Peter Hurford]], organist and composer, 88<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.rhinegold.co.uk/choir_organ/peter-hurford-dies-aged-88/ |title= Peter Hurford dies at 88 |last= Bradshaw |first= Melissa |date= 4 March 2019 |website= Rhinegold Publishing |access-date= 5 March 2019}}</ref>\n* [[4 March]] \u2013 [[Keith Flint]], singer, musician ([[The Prodigy]]), 49<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-47442312|title=The Prodigy's Keith Flint dies aged 49|author=Mark Savage|date=4 March 2019|work=BBC News|accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref>\n* [[6 March]] \u2013 [[Grayston Burgess]], countertenor and conductor, 86<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2019/04/15/grayston-burgess-counter-tenor-led-way-introducing-elizabethan/ | title=Grayston Burgess, counter-tenor who led the way in introducing the Elizabethan singing style to modern audiences \u2013 obituary | work=The Daily Telegraph | author= | date=15 April 2019 | accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n* [[26 March]] \u2013 [[Ranking Roger]], ska musician, 56 (cancer)<ref>{{cite web|