ic FM|access-date=23 April 2019}}</ref>\n* [[25 April]] \u2013 The Development Management Sub-Committee of the City of Edinburgh Council approves plans for the construction of Dunard Centre, the first purpose-built music and performance venue in Edinburgh in over 100 years.<ref>{{cite press release | url=https://www.eif.co.uk/festival-guide/news-and-blogs/approval-for-edinburghs-dunard-centre-a-new-music-and-performance-venue | title=Approval for Edinburgh's Dunard Centre - a new music and performance venue | publisher=Edinburgh International Festival | date=25 April 2019 | accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n* [[29 April]] \u2013 The PRS Foundation announces that Vanessa Reed is to stand down as its executive director, effective with the summer of 2019.<ref>{{cite press release | url=https://prsfoundation.com/2019/04/29/vanessa-reed-appointed-president-and-ceo-of-new-music-usa/ | title=Vanessa Reed appointed President and CEO of New Music USA | publisher=PRS Foundation | date=29 April 2019 | accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n* [[7 May]] \u2013 BBC Radio 3 announces the musicians for its New Generation Artists scheme from 2019-2021:<ref>{{cite press release | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/new-generation-artists-2019 | title=Next wave of star musicians announced as BBC Radio 3 reveals New Generation Artists 2019-2021 | publisher=BBC | date=7 May 2019 | accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n** Eric Lu, piano\n** Alexander Gadjiev, piano\n** Timothy Ridout, viola\n** Consone Quartet\n** Johan Dalene, violin\n** Rob Luft, jazz guitar\n** Ema Nikoslovska, mezzo-soprano\n* [[10 May]] \u2013 The [[Philharmonia Orchestra]] announces that Helen Sprott is to stand down as its managing director.<ref>{{cite press release | url=https://www.philharmonia.co.uk/news/article/60/helen_sprott_to_step_down_as_managing_director_of_the_philharmonia_orchestra | title=Helen Sprott to step down as Managing Director of the Philharmonia Orchestra | publisher=Philharmonia Orchestra