cy Tartaglione|website=Deadline|access-date=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n*''[[Cats (2019 film)|Cats]]'', starring [[James Corden]], [[Idris Elba]], [[Ian McKellen]] and [[Judi Dench]], with music by [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]], due for release on 20 December.<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cats-movie-gets-december-2019-release-date-1138971 'Cats' Movie Adaptation Sets December 2019 Release Date]</ref>\n*''[[Rocketman (film)|Rocketman]]'', starring [[Taron Egerton]], produced by [[Elton John]], [[David Furnish]] and [[Matthew Vaughn]]<ref>http://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/104521/taron-egerton-to-play-sir-elton-john-in-upcoming-biopic/</ref>\n*''[[Yesterday (2019 film)|Yesterday]]'', starring [[Himesh Patel]] and [[Ed Sheeran]], with songs by [[Paul McCartney]] and [[John Lennon]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Itzkoff |first1=Dave |title=The Long and Winding Road to \u2018Yesterday,\u2019 a Film Full of Beatles Music |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/28/movies/yesterday-movie-beatles-songs.html |publisher=New York Times |date=June 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Film scores and incidental music==\n===Film===\n*[[Soumik Datta]] - ''Around India with a Movie Camera''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://icarusfilms.com/if-ar|title=Around India with a Movie Camera|website=Icarus Films|access-date=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Steven Price (composer)|Steven Price]] - ''[[Wonder Park]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/07/steven-price-scoring-netflixs-our-planet/|title=Steven Price Scoring Netflix\u2019s \u2018Our Planet\u2019|website=Film Music Reporter|access-date=5 January 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Vik Sharma]] & [[Graham Coxon]] - ''[[Fighting with My Family]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/BWW-Interview-Composer-Vik-Sharma-Discusses-His-Score-For-FIGHTING-WITH-MY-FAMILY-20190216|title=BWW Interview: Composer Vik Sharma Discusses His Score For FIGHTING WITH MY FAMILY|website=Broadway World|access-date=29 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Television==